My suitcase wouldn't even fit between the bed and the TV, I had to lift it over.	But there is a good bar/gelateria around the corner on Via Sardegna where we went for gelato, Cokes, snacks, etc., instead of raiding the minibar in our room.	The only recomendation would be to upgrade the TV's and add CNN as one of their channel selections.	The bed was so comfortable, pillows were like from the TV advert.	It is on the Via Venetto and right outside of the Villa Borguese Park, where I went running every morning and you have one of Fodor's pick for museums in Rome.